opedia of the Islamic World|editor=John L. Esposito|publisher=Oxford University Press|location=Oxford|year=2009|url=http://www.oxfordislamicstudies.com/print/opr/t236/e0185|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite encyclopedia|ref=harv |first=Ronald L. |last=Nettler|title=Dhimm\u012b|encyclopedia=The Oxford Encyclopedia of the Islamic World|editor=John L. Esposito|year=2009|url=http://www.oxfordreference.com/view/10.1093/acref/9780195305135.001.0001/acref-9780195305135-e-0194|url-access=subscription |doi=10.1093/acref/9780195305135.001.0001 |isbn=9780195305135 }}\n* {{Cite book |first=Felicitas |last=Opwis |year=2007 |title=Islamic Law and Legal Change: The Concept of Maslaha in Classical and Contemporary Legal Theory |editor=Abbas Amanat |editor2=Frank Griffel |volume=Shari'a: Islamic Law in the Contemporary Context |publisher=Stanford University Press |edition=Kindle |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |ref=harv |first1=Jan Michiel |last1=Otto |year=2008 |title=Sharia and National Law in Muslim Countries: Tensions and Opportunities for Dutch and EU Foreign Policy |publisher=Amsterdam University Press |isbn=978-9087280482 |url=https://openaccess.leidenuniv.nl/bitstream/handle/1887/20694/Sharia%20and%20national%20Law%20in%20Muslim%20countries.pdf}}\n* {{cite book |ref=harv |editor1-first=Jan Michiel |editor1-last=Otto |year=2010 |title=Sharia Incorporated: A Comparative Overview of the Legal Systems of Twelve Muslim Countries in Past and Present |publisher=Leiden University Press |isbn=978-9400600171}}\n* {{cite encyclopedia|ref=harv |first=Intisar A.|last=Rabb|title=Law. Courts|encyclopedia=The Oxford Encyclopedia of the Islamic World|editor=John L. Esposito|publisher=Oxford University Press|location=Oxford|year=2009|url=http://www.oxfordislamicstudies.com/article/opr/t236/e0473}}\n* {{cite encyclopedia |ref=harv |first=Intisar A. |last=Rabb |title=Fiqh |encyclopedia=The Oxford Encyclopedia of the Islamic World |editor=John L. Esposito |publisher=Oxford University Press |location=Oxford |year=2009b |doi=10.1093/acref/9780195305135.001.0001|isbn=9780195305135 }}\n* {{cite encyclopedia |ref=harv |first=Intisar A. |last=Rabb |title=Ijtih\u0101d |encyclopedia=The Oxford Encyclopedia of the Islamic World |editor=John L. Esposito |publisher=Oxford University Press |location=Oxford |year=2009c |doi=10.1093/acref/9780195305135.001.0001 |isbn=9780195305135 }}\n* {{cite encyclopedia|ref=harv |first=Intisar A.|last=Rabb|title=Law. Civil Law|encyclopedia=The Oxford Encyclopedia of the Islamic World|editor=John L. Esposito|publisher=Oxford University Press|location=Oxford|year=2009d|url=http://www.oxfordislamicstudies.com/article/opr/t236/e0473}}\n* {{Cite encyclopedia|last1=Schacht|first1=Joseph|last2=Layish|first2=Aharon| year=2000| title=\u1e6cal\u0101\u1e33|encyclopedia=Encyclopaedia of Islam| edition=2nd|publisher=Brill |editor1=P. Bearman|editor2= Th. Bianquis|editor3= C.E. Bosworth|editor4= E. van Donzel|editor5= W.P. Heinrichs|volume=10|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite encyclopedia |ref=harv |first=Irene |last=Schneider |title=Fiqh |encyclopedia=The Oxford Encyclopedia of Islam and Politics |publisher=Oxford University Press |editor=Emad El-Din Shahin |year=2014 |doi=10.1093/acref:oiso/9780199739356.001.0001|isbn=9780199739356 }}\n* {{cite encyclopedia|first=Devin J.|last=Stewart|title=Shari'a|editor=Gerhard B\u00f6wering, Patricia Crone|encyclopedia=The Princeton Encyclopedia of Islamic Political Thought|publisher=Princeton University Press|year=2013|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite encyclopedia|first=Silvia|last=Tellenbach|year=2015|title=Islamic Criminal Law|encyclopedia=The Oxford Handbook of Criminal Law|editor1=Markus D. Dubber|editor2= Tatjana Hornle|publisher= Oxford University Press|ref=harv}} {{ISBN|978-0199673599}}\n* {{Cite encyclopedia|first=J\u00f6rn|last=Thielmann|title=\u1e24isba (modern times)|encyclopedia=Encyclopaedia of Islam|edition=3rd|editor1=Kate Fleet|editor2=Gudrun Kr\u00e4mer|editor3=Denis Matringe|editor4=John Nawas|editor5=Everett Rowson|publisher=Brill|