f service, you will see the committees of the Senate, House (Standing with Subcommittees, Select and Special) and Joint and after the committee pages, you will see the House/Senate committee assignments in the directory, on the committees section of the House and Senate in the Official Congressional Directory, the committee's members on the first row on the left side shows the chairman of the committee and on the right side shows the ranking member of the committee.\n\n===Senate===\n\n* [[United States Senate Select Committee on the Additional Accommodations for the Library of Congress|Additional Accommodations for the Library of Congress]] (Select) (Chairman: [[Thomas S. Martin]])\n* [[United States Senate Committee on Agriculture|Agriculture and Forestry]] (Chairman: [[Redfield Proctor]])\n* [[United States Senate Committee on Appropriations|Appropriations]] (Chairman: [[William B. Allison]])\n* [[United States Senate Committee to Audit and Control the Contingent Expenses of the Senate|Audit and Control the Contingent Expenses of the Senate]] (Chairman: [[John Kean (New Jersey politician)|John Kean]])\n* [[United States Senate Committee on Canadian Relations|Canadian Relations]] (Chairman: [[Winthrop Murray Crane]])\n* [[United States Senate Committee on the Census|Census]] (Chairman: [[Chester I. Long]])\n* [[United States Senate Committee on Civil Service|Civil Service and Retrenchment]] (Chairman: [[George C. Perkins]])\n* [[United States Senate Committee on Claims|Claims]] (Chairman: [[Charles W. Fulton]])\n* [[United States Senate Committee on Coast and Insular Survey|Coast and Insular Survey]] (Chairman: [[Samuel H. Piles]])\n* [[United States Senate Committee on Coast Defenses|Coast Defenses]] (Chairman: [[Philander C. Knox]])\n* [[United States Senate Committee on Commerce|Commerce]] (Chairman: [[William P. Frye]])\n* [[United States Senate Committee on Corporations Organized in the District of Columbia|Corporations Organized in the District of Columbia]] 