yball team|Serbia]]\n| medaltemplates   =\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Men's European Volleyball Championship|European Championship]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2019 Men's European Volleyball Championship|2019 Belgium/France/Netherlands/Slovenia]]|}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2011 Men's European Volleyball Championship|2011 Austria/Czech Republic]]|}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[2017 Men's European Volleyball Championship|2017 Poland]]|}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Volleyball World League|World League]]}}\n{{Medal|Gold|[[2016 FIVB Volleyball World League|2016 Krak\u00f3w]]|}}\n{{MedalSilver|[[2015 FIVB Volleyball World League|2015 Rio de Janeiro]]|}}\n}}\n\n'''Uro\u0161 Kova\u010devi\u0107''' ({{lang-sr-cyrl|\u0423\u0440\u043e\u0448 \u041a\u043e\u0432\u0430\u0447\u0435\u0432\u0438\u045b}}, born 6 May 1993) is a [[Serbia|Serbian]] [[volleyball]] player, a member of [[Serbia men's national volleyball team]] and [[Italy|Italian]] club [[Trentino Volley]], gold medalist of the [[2016 FIVB Volleyball World League|2016 World League]], [[2011 Men's European Volleyball Championship|European Champion 2011]], [[2019 Men's European Volleyball Championship|European Champion 2019]].\n\n==Personal life==\nHe has two older brothers: Savo and [[Nikola Kova\u010devi\u0107|Nikola]] (born 1983). Nikola is also a [[volleyball player]].\n\n===National team===\nHe is a gold medalist of [[2011 Men's European Volleyball Championship|European Championship 2011]].<ref>[http://www.cev.eu/Competition-Area/CompetitionNews.aspx?ID=14&NewsID=11000&TagType=0&TagContent=0&NewsType=0&Paging=0&Sd=1/1/1900&Ed=1/1/1900 ''Serbia is the 2011 European champion!''] \u2013 cev.eu \u2013 18-09-2011</ref> In 2011 Kova\u010devi\u0107 received the [[Awards of Olympic Committee of Serbia|award]] from [[Olympic Committee of Serbia]] and [[DSL Sport]] for the best young athlete.<ref>[http://www.mondo.rs/s228716/Ostali_sportovi/Sport-_Novak_Djokovic_ponovo_najbolji.html ''\"Sport\": Novak \u0110okovi\u0107 ponovo najbolji''] \u2013 mondo.rs \u2013 26-12-2011</ref> He was a member of the national team at the [[2012 Summer Olympics]] in [[London]]. On July 19, 2015 [[Serbia men's national volleyball team|Serbian national team]] with him in squad went to the final of [[2015 FIVB Volleyball World League|World League]], but they lost with [[France men's national volleyball team|France]] 0\u20133 and achieved silver medal.<ref>[http://worldleague.2015.fivb.com/en/intercontinental-group1/news/france-upset-serbia-to-claim-first-world?id=55058 ''France upset Serbia to claim first World League title''] \u2013 fivb.org \u2013 19-07-2015</ref><ref>[http://worldleague.2015.fivb.com/en/intercontinental-group1/news/france-prevail-over-serbia-to-claim-gold?id=55060 ''France prevail over Serbia to claim gold; USA finish third''] \u2013 fivb.org \u2013 19-07-2015</ref> He was named MVP of the [[2019 Men's European Volleyball Championship|2019 European Championship]] where Serbia won the gold medal.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0423\u0440\u043e\u0448 \u041a\u043e\u0432\u0430\u0447\u0435\u0432\u0438\u045b \u041c\u0412\u041f \u0448\u0430\u043c\u043f\u0438\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0442\u0430 |url=http://www.rts.rs/page/sport/ci/story/34/odbojka/3678294/uros-kovacevic-mvp-sampionata.html |accessdate=3 October 2019 |work=www.rts.rs |date=29 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Sporting achievements==\n* '''[[CEV Cup]]'''\n** [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] [[2018\u201319 Men's CEV Cup|2018/2019]] \u2013 with [[Trentino Volley|Itas Trentino]]\n\n* '''[[CEV Challenge Cup]]'''\n** [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] [[2015\u201316 CEV Challenge Cup|2015/2016]] \u2013 with [[BluVolley Verona|Calzedonia Verona]]\n\n* '''[[FIVB Volleyball Men's Club World Championship|FIVB Club World Championship]]'''\n** [[File:Gold medal world centered-2.svg|16px]] [[2018 FIVB Volleyball Men's Club World Championship|Poland 2018]] \u2013 with [[Trentino Volley|Itas Trentino]]\n\n* '''[[AVC Club Volleyball Championship|AVC Asian Club Championship]]'''\n** [[File:Silver medal asia.sv